1
00:00:06,750 --> 00:00:09,333
[ice shatters]

2
00:00:09,416 --> 00:00:10,416
[Puck crying]

3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,416
I'm sorry...

4
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,875
s-so sorry.

5
00:00:14,958 --> 00:00:15,708
[crying]

6
00:00:15,791 --> 00:00:19,416
EMILIA: Tell me,
why are you crying?

7
00:00:20,166 --> 00:00:24,083
- Because I just
left you all alone.

8
00:00:24,166 --> 00:00:26,625
- I don't understand.
What do you mean?

9
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:28,416
- Because I--

10
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:31,083
I couldn't--

11
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:33,083
I couldn't find you
all this time.

12
00:00:33,166 --> 00:00:36,500
- Easy. I'm right here, okay?

13
00:00:36,583 --> 00:00:39,333
- [continues crying]

14
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:43,166
- By the way, what's your name?

15
00:00:44,375 --> 00:00:47,125
- Oh, yeah.

16
00:00:47,208 --> 00:00:49,041
I guess you don't know it,
do you?

17
00:00:50,333 --> 00:00:52,041
[music playing]

18
00:01:04,416 --> 00:01:06,375
[birds chirping]

19
00:01:07,875 --> 00:01:09,625
[footsteps crunching]

20
00:01:09,708 --> 00:01:11,833
EMILIA: I know this is
just a dream world,

21
00:01:11,916 --> 00:01:14,875
but I can smell the air.
I can even feel the dirt.

22
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:18,291
That's so strange, isn't it?

23
00:01:18,375 --> 00:01:19,625
Are you listening?

24
00:01:19,708 --> 00:01:20,916
Hey, Echidna?

25
00:01:21,916 --> 00:01:23,791
[leaves rustling]

26
00:01:23,875 --> 00:01:24,833
[gasps]

27
00:01:24,916 --> 00:01:25,416
I'm sorry!

28
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,333
Are you all right?

29
00:01:27,416 --> 00:01:28,791
Was I walking
a little too quickly?

30
00:01:28,875 --> 00:01:31,500
- Oh, save your fake sympathy.

31
00:01:31,583 --> 00:01:34,666
You don't think those words
will change my attitude, do you?

32
00:01:34,750 --> 00:01:36,000
If so,
then you're quite foolish.

33
00:01:36,083 --> 00:01:38,875
- [sighs] I was
genuinely worried about you.

34
00:01:38,958 --> 00:01:42,625
- I need none of your concern
whatsoever.

35
00:01:42,708 --> 00:01:46,250
There were a few too many dreams
happening at once. That's all.

36
00:01:46,333 --> 00:01:47,750
It will adjust itself soon

37
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:50,541
slowly, but surely. See?

38
00:01:50,625 --> 00:01:51,208
- [gasps]

39
00:01:51,291 --> 00:01:53,500
- Consider the name "dreamworld"

40
00:01:53,583 --> 00:01:55,666
to be merely
a figurative expression.

41
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:58,125
More accurately,
it's a separate world

42
00:01:58,208 --> 00:02:00,000
replicating the memories
and reflecting the consciousness

43
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:03,041
of those who choose
to undergo the trial.

44
00:02:03,125 --> 00:02:05,791
- Thanks for that.
I appreciate the explanation,

45
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:07,541
even though you don't like me.

46
00:02:07,625 --> 00:02:09,958
- Hmph. Just don't get
any ridiculous ideas

47
00:02:10,041 --> 00:02:12,791
about me actually being
a nice person or anything.

48
00:02:12,875 --> 00:02:14,208
It's simply my nature

49
00:02:14,291 --> 00:02:16,458
to answer any questions
that are asked of me.

50
00:02:16,541 --> 00:02:18,166
I understand.

51
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:23,208
- Do you remember the pathetic
struggle you endured

52
00:02:23,291 --> 00:02:25,708
the last time
you attempted the trial?

53
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:27,375
- I was so helpless then.

54
00:02:27,458 --> 00:02:30,208
I can't even argue
with your description of it.

55
00:02:30,291 --> 00:02:32,583
I guess
I covered up my memories

56
00:02:32,666 --> 00:02:34,208
because I didn't want
to see them.

57
00:02:34,291 --> 00:02:38,708
Maybe that's why I can't even
recall one of them on my own.

58
00:02:38,791 --> 00:02:41,625
Everything's just so fuzzy.

59
00:02:41,708 --> 00:02:44,041
Even now,
I'm still not prepared.

60
00:02:44,125 --> 00:02:47,458
- Then it would be no surprise
if you failed again, right?

61
00:02:47,541 --> 00:02:51,416
Making an excuse before you
even start is awfully defeatist.

62
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,250
- No, it's not that.

63
00:02:53,333 --> 00:02:57,000
I've thought of a way to use
this place to ready myself.

64
00:02:58,041 --> 00:02:59,791
[birds chirping]

65
00:03:00,791 --> 00:03:02,958
ECHIDNA: I'm assuming
this is no ordinary tree.

66
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:04,875
There was something
you desperately wanted

67
00:03:04,958 --> 00:03:07,708
to keep locked up inside it.

68
00:03:07,791 --> 00:03:09,416
- This is the Princess Room.

69
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:13,416
I was often sent here to play
back when I was little.

70
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,833
Oh, right.
I can't touch the door.

71
00:03:15,916 --> 00:03:18,375
Could we just walk
through it instead?

72
00:03:19,916 --> 00:03:20,875
Huh?

73
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,375
[music playing]

74
00:03:30,458 --> 00:03:32,583
[gasps]

75
00:03:39,208 --> 00:03:42,708
- The young one
is clearly you, isn't it?

76
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:43,833
Even though you weren't
aware of anything yet,

77
00:03:43,916 --> 00:03:47,500
you look
so annoyingly carefree.

78
00:03:47,583 --> 00:03:49,458
- Are you going to complain
about me at every age?

79
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:52,625
Besides, now I--

80
00:03:52,708 --> 00:03:53,375
[sighs]

81
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:04,083
It's my Mother Fortuna.

82
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:08,750
- Emilia, I need to go
and take care of something,

83
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:11,583
so you stay here in this room,
and be good, all right?

84
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:13,833
- Is it
something important again?

85
00:04:13,916 --> 00:04:14,875
- [laughs]

86
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:19,333
That silver hair of yours
is exactly like my brother's.

87
00:04:19,416 --> 00:04:20,791
However, I believe
your gentle features

88
00:04:20,875 --> 00:04:23,500
come from your mother's side,

89
00:04:23,583 --> 00:04:25,875
'cause everyone
from my side has mean eyes

90
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:29,083
Oh, no! They're two of the
prettiest ones I've ever seen!

91
00:04:29,166 --> 00:04:32,125
- That woman's Mother Fortuna,
my father's younger sister.

92
00:04:32,208 --> 00:04:35,041
My real parents
were always too busy

93
00:04:35,125 --> 00:04:37,125
with their responsibilities
to make time for me,

94
00:04:37,208 --> 00:04:40,375
which meant that most of my days
were spent in her care.

95
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:45,041
[door creaks]

96
00:04:45,125 --> 00:04:46,083
[bolt clanks]

97
00:04:48,916 --> 00:04:49,708
- [moans]

98
00:04:49,791 --> 00:04:52,500
I'm so bored!

99
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,666
Why does she
hide everything from me?

100
00:04:54,750 --> 00:04:56,833
Mother says lying
and secrets are wrong!

101
00:04:56,916 --> 00:04:57,916
Right?!

102
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:01,291
I wish I could go outside.

103
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,041
Huh?

104
00:05:07,583 --> 00:05:08,458
Uh, hi.

105
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:11,625
[gasps]

106
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:14,041
Hey! Hold on! No fair!

107
00:05:16,625 --> 00:05:18,875
- [breeze blowing]
- Huh?

108
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:21,666
[gasps]

109
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:25,041
[birds chirping]

110
00:05:25,125 --> 00:05:27,083
[grunting]

111
00:05:28,708 --> 00:05:29,666
Ah.

112
00:05:31,125 --> 00:05:33,833
Mother Fortuna and everyone else
keeps secrets from me,

113
00:05:33,916 --> 00:05:35,541
so this should make us even!

114
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:36,541
[grunts]

115
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:40,791
[village chatter]

116
00:05:43,041 --> 00:05:44,458
Sneaky, sneak.

117
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:45,583
[gasps]

118
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:46,583
[yelps]

119
00:05:46,666 --> 00:05:47,875
[grunts]

120
00:05:52,125 --> 00:05:53,833
[music playing]

121
00:05:58,166 --> 00:05:59,583
FORTUNA: I want to thank you.

122
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:02,583
You've done so much for us
time and time again.

123
00:06:02,666 --> 00:06:04,041
- That isn't necessary.
I know we've brought you

124
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:07,000
more than your share
of inconveniences.

125
00:06:07,083 --> 00:06:10,166
- Well, the same could also
be said for us, Geuse.

126
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:12,916
- Also...

127
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,833
I know that I ask this
every time we meet,

128
00:06:16,916 --> 00:06:18,708
but does the seal remain intact?

129
00:06:18,791 --> 00:06:21,666
- Yes, don't worry.
There have been no changes.

130
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,000
And it needs to stay that way.

131
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,541
If the worst were to happen,

132
00:06:24,625 --> 00:06:26,958
I could never face
my brother and sister.

133
00:06:27,041 --> 00:06:29,458
- Your brother and his wife,
you mean?

134
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,291
- It's all right.
I'm aware of that.

135
00:06:31,375 --> 00:06:34,166
But no matter the circumstances,
I mustn't forget

136
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:37,666
the responsibility
I've been tasked to carry.

137
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:41,041
I don't want to abandon it
or see it partway.

138
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:41,791
Don't you feel the same?

139
00:06:41,875 --> 00:06:44,958
- Well, actually...

140
00:06:45,041 --> 00:06:45,958
[sighs] to be completely
honest with you,

141
00:06:46,041 --> 00:06:48,458
I don't have anything else.

142
00:06:48,541 --> 00:06:50,416
So I suppose it's a different

143
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:51,958
sense of responsibility
from yours.

144
00:06:52,041 --> 00:06:55,791
Obsession, regret...

145
00:06:55,875 --> 00:06:58,708
I'm clinging to things that
might as well be delusions.

146
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:01,000
- [sighs]

147
00:07:01,083 --> 00:07:03,833
Thanks to the spirits,

148
00:07:03,916 --> 00:07:06,750
the seasons don't change
very much in the forest,

149
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,000
but you continue to bring us
things like clothing and
books.

150
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:11,916
We truly appreciate it.

151
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:14,750
Thank you, as always.

152
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:16,125
- [sighs]

153
00:07:16,208 --> 00:07:18,750
Truthfully, I don't agree
with forcing all of you

154
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:21,083
to live in such
an inconvenient place like this.

155
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,833
It won't ever seem right to me.

156
00:07:22,916 --> 00:07:25,750
- Come on. Don't just call it
"a place like this."

157
00:07:25,833 --> 00:07:29,166
Think you're forgetting that
everybody here loves the
forest.

158
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:31,000
- Miss Fortuna!
- Eh?

159
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:33,791
- All the items
have been transferred.

160
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:36,000
- Thank you, Archi.
I appreciate it.

161
00:07:36,083 --> 00:07:37,708
- I can see you're only growing

162
00:07:37,791 --> 00:07:39,333
more and more dependable,
aren't you?

163
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:42,166
- As part of the next generation
of forest dwellers,

164
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:44,583
I know I can't be regarded
as a novice forever.

165
00:07:44,666 --> 00:07:47,750
- I pray that your good health
will persevere,

166
00:07:47,833 --> 00:07:49,583
for the forest and the seal,

167
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:52,958
for your family, and of course
for yourself as well.

168
00:07:59,125 --> 00:08:00,708
Oh, yes,

169
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,083
I almost forgot to ask you.

170
00:08:02,166 --> 00:08:05,083
About Miss Emilia,
does she remain in good health?

171
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,041
- [gasps]

172
00:08:06,125 --> 00:08:07,250
- No need to worry.

173
00:08:07,333 --> 00:08:10,208
She's growing into
a very kindhearted

174
00:08:10,291 --> 00:08:12,041
and healthy young lady.

175
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,708
But I apologize.

176
00:08:13,791 --> 00:08:15,750
I still can't allow her
to meet you.

177
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:16,750
- It's all right.

178
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,541
As long as I know
Miss Emilia's growing up safe

179
00:08:19,625 --> 00:08:21,125
and in good health,
then that'll be enough.

180
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,875
A sinner such as myself

181
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:26,750
wouldn't ever dare to ask
for anything more than
that.

182
00:08:29,125 --> 00:08:30,250
- Bishop RomanÃ©e-Conti...
- [gasps]

183
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:31,708
- are you ready?

184
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:34,125
- Yes. I'm all finished here.

185
00:08:34,208 --> 00:08:37,125
It's time for us transgressors
to be on our way.

186
00:08:37,208 --> 00:08:40,625
Miss Fortuna,
until next time then.

187
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:42,375
- Even if no one else here
will say it,

188
00:08:42,458 --> 00:08:46,208
please know that we're
extremely grateful to you,

189
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:47,125
and I truly mean that.

190
00:08:47,208 --> 00:08:49,083
- That's kind of you to say.

191
00:08:49,166 --> 00:08:51,416
Your words of praise alone

192
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:54,500
would surely carry me through
a hundred years of turmoil.

193
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:03,958
[wind blowing]

194
00:09:04,041 --> 00:09:05,416
- [sighs]

195
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,583
- Miss Fortuna,
are you feeling tired or--

196
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:11,750
- Of course not! Don't treat me
like such an old lady.

197
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:13,208
I know I may seem elderly

198
00:09:13,291 --> 00:09:15,166
compared to
a young boy like you,

199
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:16,791
but I'm still in good shape.

200
00:09:16,875 --> 00:09:19,208
- Th--No, that wasn't
what I meant at all!

201
00:09:19,291 --> 00:09:21,125
I just thought
this must be hard

202
00:09:21,208 --> 00:09:23,833
when you also have
the forest dweller duties.

203
00:09:23,916 --> 00:09:26,791
- Then maybe I'll take advantage
of your kindness

204
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:29,291
and let you handle
the rest of them.

205
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:32,166
Right now I need to go
and free a little princess

206
00:09:32,250 --> 00:09:34,166
who must be getting
pretty bored.

207
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:36,083
- [gasps]

208
00:09:36,166 --> 00:09:37,291
What do I do? What do I do?

209
00:09:37,375 --> 00:09:38,958
What do I do?
What do I do?

210
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:41,000
What do--[yelps]

211
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:42,125
What do I do? What do--

212
00:09:42,208 --> 00:09:44,791
What do I do? What do I do?

213
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:46,208
[gasps] Oh, no.

214
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:48,708
What do I do? What do I do?

215
00:09:48,791 --> 00:09:52,333
[gasps]

216
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:55,208
[energy surges]

217
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:56,750
Wow.

218
00:09:56,833 --> 00:09:58,916
- Emilia, are you awake?

219
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,833
- Uh, y-yes, I'm awake!

220
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:02,916
But...[sighs]

221
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:04,333
- But what?

222
00:10:04,416 --> 00:10:06,000
- Why are you so flustered?
- [glass clatters]

223
00:10:06,083 --> 00:10:07,000
[gasps]

224
00:10:08,916 --> 00:10:11,958
- Um, I-I'm sorry.

225
00:10:12,041 --> 00:10:14,833
I wanted to draw, but I
spilled the ink everywhere.

226
00:10:14,916 --> 00:10:17,166
- Ah, dear.

227
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:20,291
Mother Fortuna, I-I'm sorry.

228
00:10:20,375 --> 00:10:22,958
Honestly, you worry
about things too much.

229
00:10:23,041 --> 00:10:25,083
You don't need to be so afraid.

230
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:27,833
I'm not angry, okay?

231
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:29,458
You didn't hurt yourself,
did you?

232
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:33,083
[cloth flutters]

233
00:10:33,166 --> 00:10:34,208
- What's wrong?

234
00:10:34,291 --> 00:10:38,750
- Nothing. It's nothing.

235
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:41,500
I just really missed you today.
That's all.

236
00:10:43,125 --> 00:10:44,708
- Uh...

237
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:47,708
- You spoiled girl.

238
00:10:47,791 --> 00:10:48,833
Hey. Wanna know something?

239
00:10:48,916 --> 00:10:49,833
- Hmm?

240
00:10:50,958 --> 00:10:53,291
- I love you.

241
00:10:55,875 --> 00:10:58,916
ECHIDNA: Perhaps the sights you
locked deep within your heart

242
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,125
have begun to overlap,

243
00:11:00,208 --> 00:11:03,125
intertwining with scenes
from your memories a bit.

244
00:11:03,208 --> 00:11:04,583
- I'm shocked.

245
00:11:04,666 --> 00:11:06,833
I thought you'd have
some stinging comments ready,

246
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:09,250
mean and petty things
to say about Mother and me.

247
00:11:09,333 --> 00:11:11,541
- Even if that's
what you thought I would do,

248
00:11:11,625 --> 00:11:13,833
I wouldn't recommend
putting that out in the open

249
00:11:13,916 --> 00:11:14,750
and saying so.

250
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:16,958
My opinion of you
is already low enough.

251
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:18,375
And with these
petty accusations,

252
00:11:18,458 --> 00:11:20,416
you're making it
plummet even further.

253
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:23,041
- Oh, no need to worry.
I hadn't planned

254
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:25,083
on telling anyone about this
to begin with.

255
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:28,416
- For better or for worse,

256
00:11:28,500 --> 00:11:30,791
it seems the influence
that boy's had over you

257
00:11:30,875 --> 00:11:31,208
has grown rather strong.

258
00:11:31,291 --> 00:11:33,291
- You think so?

259
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:34,916
Thanks for telling me.

260
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,000
- [sighs]

261
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:39,083
Anyway,
back to the task at hand.

262
00:11:39,166 --> 00:11:40,291
You've recalled your mother,

263
00:11:40,375 --> 00:11:42,375
some people you knew,
and that so-called fairy.

264
00:11:42,458 --> 00:11:45,916
Are you ready
to face your past now?

265
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,416
- No, not yet.

266
00:11:47,500 --> 00:11:49,000
- [gasps]

267
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:52,416
- There are still some
important memories I'm missing.

268
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,958
- What more could there be?

269
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:57,875
- There's the seal.

270
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:03,333
- Little fairy, let's get going.

271
00:12:03,416 --> 00:12:04,958
We're escaping again today.

272
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:07,458
[gasps]

273
00:12:07,541 --> 00:12:09,916
- Hello? Emilia?
- [yelps]

274
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:13,125
- Hmm? Is something the matter?

275
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:15,125
- Nope! I'm just fine.

276
00:12:15,208 --> 00:12:16,416
What was it you needed, Archi?

277
00:12:16,500 --> 00:12:19,208
- Well, first thing's first.

278
00:12:19,291 --> 00:12:21,666
I thought I'd bring
some snacks over for you.

279
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:24,208
Now eat these up,
and be a good girl, all right?

280
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:27,791
- Okay. Thanks.

281
00:12:27,875 --> 00:12:30,375
Archi's been
such a worrywart lately,

282
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:32,625
so I need to be extra careful.

283
00:12:32,708 --> 00:12:33,625
[yelps]

284
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:34,833
[grunts]

285
00:12:34,916 --> 00:12:37,833
Geuse's group
is here again today.

286
00:12:37,916 --> 00:12:39,875
I thought
whatever they were hiding

287
00:12:39,958 --> 00:12:41,333
would be something fun.

288
00:12:41,416 --> 00:12:43,458
Mother and the others
are really weird.

289
00:12:44,458 --> 00:12:45,250
FORTUNA: I have to say

290
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:48,000
Emilia's been
so full of energy lately.

291
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:50,416
She's always coming home
with her clothes all muddy.

292
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:52,666
- [laughs] That she's so lively
can only be a good thing.

293
00:12:52,750 --> 00:12:55,500
I'll bring some new clothes
for her soon.

294
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,500
- You've already done so much.

295
00:12:57,583 --> 00:13:00,833
I'm sorry to be asking
for even more.

296
00:13:00,916 --> 00:13:02,500
But do you have
adult clothes, too?

297
00:13:02,583 --> 00:13:03,166
- Yes, of course we do.

298
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:05,833
So why not take a look?

299
00:13:05,916 --> 00:13:08,958
I'm sure we have
something
that would be lovely on
you.

300
00:13:09,041 --> 00:13:11,000
- [gasps] Hold on.

301
00:13:11,083 --> 00:13:12,833
We may have known
each other a long time,

302
00:13:12,916 --> 00:13:14,375
but there's no need
to embarrass me

303
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:16,125
- with comments like that!
- [grunts]

304
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:17,625
I only spoke
what I felt to be the truth.

305
00:13:17,708 --> 00:13:21,208
Was there something strange
about how I said it?

306
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:23,958
- [sighs]

307
00:13:24,041 --> 00:13:25,125
- Uh...

308
00:13:25,208 --> 00:13:26,125
eh?

309
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:27,833
- [gasps]

310
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:31,291
Hey, uh, what are you doing?

311
00:13:31,375 --> 00:13:34,041
- Oh, I-I was just
remembering something.

312
00:13:34,125 --> 00:13:35,166
There was once a time

313
00:13:35,250 --> 00:13:37,083
when you seemed unhappy
while talking to me,

314
00:13:37,166 --> 00:13:39,541
and it turned out
you had a rather high fever.

315
00:13:39,625 --> 00:13:42,083
You're not warm now, though.

316
00:13:42,166 --> 00:13:43,416
- Come on.
You're just being silly.

317
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,083
That was decades ago.

318
00:13:45,166 --> 00:13:46,416
Stop treating me like a child!

319
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:49,291
You're so ridiculous.

320
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:51,041
- [groans]

321
00:13:51,125 --> 00:13:51,750
That stupid Geuse!

322
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:54,500
Oh, yeah!
And stupid Archi, too!

323
00:13:54,583 --> 00:13:56,208
- [sneezes]

324
00:13:56,291 --> 00:13:57,375
[groans]

325
00:13:57,458 --> 00:13:58,125
GEUSE: Tell me,

326
00:13:58,208 --> 00:14:00,291
does the seal
still remain in place?

327
00:14:00,375 --> 00:14:04,041
- Just as always, yes.

328
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:04,833
It's very conscientious of you

329
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:07,416
to check on it
each time you're here.

330
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,583
- That is my duty after all.

331
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:11,583
The state of affairs
outside the forest

332
00:14:11,666 --> 00:14:13,375
is dubious at the moment.

333
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:17,041
Perhaps my concern is baseless,
but I wanted you to be aware.

334
00:14:17,125 --> 00:14:18,958
- Of course.

335
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:21,416
- Please continue
being diligent

336
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:24,958
for Miss Emilia
and for the two of them as well.

337
00:14:25,375 --> 00:14:27,333
- Wait. What seal?

338
00:14:29,208 --> 00:14:30,166
Huh?

339
00:14:30,250 --> 00:14:31,375
[chuckles]

340
00:14:31,458 --> 00:14:34,416
Yes, please. [giggles]

341
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,458
[footsteps crunching]

342
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,500
[music playing]

343
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:56,125
ECHIDNA: A door?

344
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:58,625
Strange to see one out here.

345
00:15:02,166 --> 00:15:04,541
EMILIA: This is the seal.

346
00:15:09,708 --> 00:15:13,666
And its very existence
is the reason.

347
00:15:16,125 --> 00:15:17,083
- So you found the answer,
did you?

348
00:15:28,041 --> 00:15:30,125
- This is what they've
been talking about?

349
00:15:36,125 --> 00:15:37,375
- Some other guy saw my letter

350
00:15:37,458 --> 00:15:39,166
to the girl who I'm
in love with before she did.

351
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:41,125
[whimpers]

352
00:15:41,208 --> 00:15:43,000
My life is over.

353
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:46,083
- Aw, come on. You're way
too damn depressed about this.

354
00:15:46,166 --> 00:15:48,333
Gotta try and get ahold
of yourself, man.

355
00:15:48,416 --> 00:15:50,333
- I never imagined
that Garfiel would be there

356
00:15:50,416 --> 00:15:52,583
in the shadows
waiting to settle the score.

357
00:15:52,666 --> 00:15:54,333
- Look, you're always
hitting on her

358
00:15:54,416 --> 00:15:55,666
in front of other people,
anyway.

359
00:15:55,750 --> 00:15:57,500
So why get
so embarrassed about it

360
00:15:57,583 --> 00:15:59,500
just because you put it
in writing this time?

361
00:15:59,583 --> 00:16:02,458
- Normally I'm prepared for
her
to brush off stuff like this.

362
00:16:02,541 --> 00:16:04,125
Since that's
what always happens,

363
00:16:04,208 --> 00:16:05,333
I've gotten used to it!

364
00:16:05,416 --> 00:16:08,250
But I was going for broke
and being serious for once!

365
00:16:08,333 --> 00:16:10,500
And it was literally
a late-night love letter,

366
00:16:10,583 --> 00:16:12,208
the most embarrassing kind!

367
00:16:12,291 --> 00:16:14,666
- Hey, don't beat yourself up
about it, boss.

368
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,416
If anything, it made me wish

369
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:18,375
that I could sponge off
of your good luck.

370
00:16:18,458 --> 00:16:19,291
"In matters of love,

371
00:16:19,375 --> 00:16:21,458
follow the lingdorn's example."
Am I right?

372
00:16:21,541 --> 00:16:23,166
- I know you wanna
make me feel better,

373
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:25,000
but no matter what you say,
it still sounds

374
00:16:25,083 --> 00:16:27,125
like you're just trying
to pick a fight with me!

375
00:16:27,208 --> 00:16:29,000
[Subaru groans] It took Garfiel

376
00:16:29,083 --> 00:16:31,375
about an hour for the trial
when he went in,

377
00:16:31,458 --> 00:16:33,375
so I guess
it'll take her about the same.

378
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:36,375
- If she successfully
completes it, that is.

379
00:16:36,458 --> 00:16:37,708
[groans]

380
00:16:37,791 --> 00:16:39,541
RAM: Try to take a hint
for a change.

381
00:16:39,625 --> 00:16:41,750
- Huh? Ow!

382
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,708
- You're this oblivious, and
you call yourself a merchant?

383
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:46,250
- Comments like that
hurt a lot more

384
00:16:46,333 --> 00:16:48,416
- than a flick to the forehead.
- Anyway...

385
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,500
Miss Shima would like to have
a word with you, Barusu.

386
00:16:51,583 --> 00:16:54,000
She wants to continue
the discussion from last night.

387
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:55,833
- What did Gran--Uh, I mean,
what did the old hag

388
00:16:55,916 --> 00:16:58,625
wanna talk to you about
for so long, boss?

389
00:16:58,708 --> 00:17:00,625
- There's no point in trying
to cover it up now,

390
00:17:00,708 --> 00:17:02,375
because we all know
you're a granny's boy.

391
00:17:02,458 --> 00:17:03,666
Mostly, she told me
what happened

392
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,250
when you went
into the graveyard.

393
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:06,625
- Oh, really?

394
00:17:06,708 --> 00:17:09,458
- I had my hands full yesterday

395
00:17:09,541 --> 00:17:11,208
figuring out
how to deal with Garfiel.

396
00:17:11,291 --> 00:17:12,041
And even though
most things were sorted out,

397
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,500
we still put off
the most important part.

398
00:17:14,583 --> 00:17:16,250
RAM: What are you
referring to, exactly?

399
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,333
SUBARU: Well...

400
00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:21,000
SHIMA: It is a subject
that is quite unavoidable

401
00:17:21,083 --> 00:17:23,916
if you truly wish
to liberate the Sanctuary.

402
00:17:26,541 --> 00:17:30,166
[wind blowing]

403
00:17:31,708 --> 00:17:34,583
- [grunting]

404
00:17:35,541 --> 00:17:38,583
This door's strange.
Why won't it fall over?

405
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:41,791
I don't understand how it works.

406
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:44,750
But thanks to all of you,
I at least managed to find it!

407
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,375
Yay, everyone!

408
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:49,208
Now what?

409
00:17:49,291 --> 00:17:50,666
This whole thing
is Mother Fortuna's fault,

410
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:53,791
and it's Geuse's fault, too.

411
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,333
Nyah!

412
00:17:57,833 --> 00:18:00,791
Okay, time to go home.

413
00:18:00,875 --> 00:18:03,458
Today I think
I'll paint the sky red

414
00:18:03,541 --> 00:18:05,416
and then use white
for the whole forest!

415
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,791
[panting]

416
00:18:08,875 --> 00:18:09,708
Eh?

417
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:11,500
Hey, what's wrong?

418
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:18,416
Is something gonna happen?

419
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:20,583
[chuckles]

420
00:18:20,666 --> 00:18:21,833
[brush rustles]

421
00:18:24,791 --> 00:18:26,333
GEUSE: This is quite a problem.

422
00:18:26,416 --> 00:18:27,833
- [gasps]

423
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:31,291
- I might not make it
by the appointed time.

424
00:18:31,375 --> 00:18:32,333
Eh?

425
00:18:33,458 --> 00:18:34,500
Oh.

426
00:18:34,583 --> 00:18:36,916
And what cute little child
might this be?

427
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,416
- [whimpers]

428
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:41,333
Please, sir, I beg you

429
00:18:41,416 --> 00:18:43,791
to let me on my way
and show mercy.

430
00:18:43,875 --> 00:18:46,500
- Well, well, My goodness.

431
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:47,875
What an adorable young lady.

432
00:18:47,958 --> 00:18:49,541
[gasps]

433
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,458
- Huh?
- Wait.

434
00:18:51,541 --> 00:18:52,916
Don't tell me that you're--

435
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:56,250
No. You can't be her.

436
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:57,833
[gasps]

437
00:18:57,916 --> 00:18:58,958
- What's wrong?

438
00:18:59,541 --> 00:19:01,458
You okay, Geuse?

439
00:19:01,541 --> 00:19:03,500
- [crying]

440
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,958
Yes. I'm fine.

441
00:19:13,041 --> 00:19:14,833
Of course.

442
00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:17,708
Yes, I couldn't be better.

443
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:20,500
Nothing is wrong
in the slightest.

444
00:19:20,583 --> 00:19:21,708
Do you want to know why?

445
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:25,458
Because I--[cries]

446
00:19:25,541 --> 00:19:26,541
Because I've just...

447
00:19:26,625 --> 00:19:31,666
been granted salvation
like never before!

448
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,833
- Eh, really?

449
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,291
If you've been saved,

450
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:39,333
then why are you crying?

451
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:40,916
- It's quite simple.

452
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:43,458
I'm not crying because I'm sad.

453
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:45,375
I'm so happy,

454
00:19:45,458 --> 00:19:47,250
and I feel elated.

455
00:19:47,333 --> 00:19:48,500
I'm truly blessed.

456
00:19:48,583 --> 00:19:52,375
All of this joy can sometimes
bring warm tears to one's
eyes.

457
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:56,041
[crying]

458
00:20:02,625 --> 00:20:05,791
You cry even when you're happy?

459
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,583
It's all right, Geuse. Easy.

460
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,416
It's all right.

461
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,000
It's all right.

462
00:20:19,333 --> 00:20:20,750
- I know there are
so many things like this

463
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:22,958
that I'd forgotten.

464
00:20:23,041 --> 00:20:24,500
It's still hard.

465
00:20:24,583 --> 00:20:25,791
Not too long ago,

466
00:20:25,875 --> 00:20:27,666
I wouldn't have been able
to accept this.

467
00:20:27,750 --> 00:20:30,416
But now it's different.

468
00:20:31,541 --> 00:20:32,750
I may be scared,

469
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:33,791
but I won't shy away in fear.

470
00:20:33,875 --> 00:20:36,416
- You're opting to abandon

471
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:38,458
depending on a man
or father figure,

472
00:20:38,541 --> 00:20:42,291
even though it's so typical
of a filthy woman like you?

473
00:20:42,375 --> 00:20:42,958
- I'm sure
Subaru would forgive me

474
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:44,666
if I were to make that choice,

475
00:20:44,750 --> 00:20:47,208
but I'd still be weak,

476
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:50,208
and that's something
I don't want to just shrug off.

477
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:53,000
Besides, I don't want
all those encouraging things

478
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:55,791
he wrote for me
to end up being wrong.

479
00:20:55,875 --> 00:20:58,166
He really believes in me,

480
00:20:58,250 --> 00:20:59,833
and that's why
I can't allow myself

481
00:20:59,916 --> 00:21:03,625
to be embarrassed
by his feelings.

482
00:21:03,708 --> 00:21:04,750
- Do what you believe
to be right.

483
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,250
Regardless of your path,

484
00:21:07,333 --> 00:21:10,500
I will simply find satisfaction
in your suffering.

485
00:21:12,583 --> 00:21:14,541
- So everything is ready now?

486
00:21:14,625 --> 00:21:17,166
- That's correct,
and the warm-up round is over.

487
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:20,500
The trial that broke you once
is beginning for real.

488
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:22,458
Get ready.

489
00:21:23,666 --> 00:21:25,291
GEUSE: Please wait, Miss Emilia!

490
00:21:25,375 --> 00:21:26,750
It's dangerous
to run around like that!

491
00:21:26,833 --> 00:21:29,833
- That's a big no!

492
00:21:29,916 --> 00:21:31,625
Come on! Just try to catch me!

493
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:33,958
- [panting]

494
00:21:34,041 --> 00:21:35,541
- She's pretty mischievous,
isn't she?

495
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:38,291
At times, even we
can barely handle her.

496
00:21:38,375 --> 00:21:40,750
- It's good to be young
and full of such energy.

497
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,375
But I-I just wish

498
00:21:42,458 --> 00:21:44,458
she would avoid
doing anything too dangerous.

499
00:21:44,541 --> 00:21:46,958
If she could jump around
in her home,

500
00:21:47,041 --> 00:21:49,375
healthy and bathed in sunlight,

501
00:21:49,458 --> 00:21:51,041
with no concerns
about hurting herself

502
00:21:51,125 --> 00:21:52,041
or breaking things--

503
00:21:52,125 --> 00:21:52,875
- Geuse.
- Huh?

504
00:21:52,958 --> 00:21:55,833
- Come on.
That wouldn't exactly be easy.

505
00:21:55,916 --> 00:21:57,416
- [stammers]

506
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,916
You--You don't think so?

507
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:00,666
Well, for Miss Emilia's sake,

508
00:22:00,750 --> 00:22:02,708
I only wish
there was some way to--

509
00:22:02,791 --> 00:22:04,000
Some way to just--

510
00:22:04,083 --> 00:22:05,500
- [laughs]

511
00:22:05,583 --> 00:22:06,833
- EMILIA: Hey!
- [gasps]

512
00:22:06,916 --> 00:22:08,666
- What's gotten
into you, anyway?

513
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:10,750
Why aren't either one
of you chasing me?

514
00:22:10,833 --> 00:22:13,541
Aren't we still in the middle
of playing a game?

515
00:22:13,625 --> 00:22:16,041
- Ah, I'm so sorry. Forgive me!

516
00:22:16,125 --> 00:22:18,791
Never before have I made
such a terrible mistake!

517
00:22:18,875 --> 00:22:20,041
Now, there's no need
to spoil her like that.

518
00:22:20,125 --> 00:22:23,541
Emilia, come over here, please.

519
00:22:23,625 --> 00:22:26,083
- Okay, Mother. Be right there.

520
00:22:26,166 --> 00:22:27,416
[sighs]

521
00:22:27,500 --> 00:22:29,000
Honestly, you are so spoiled.

522
00:22:29,083 --> 00:22:30,125
Eep!

523
00:22:30,208 --> 00:22:31,750
- Right into my trap.

524
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:32,625
It looks like
you've been captured,

525
00:22:32,708 --> 00:22:34,750
which means I've
officially won the game.

526
00:22:34,833 --> 00:22:36,916
- Aw, come on. No fair!
That's cheating!

527
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,916
You're playing dirty!
Say you're sorry!

528
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:39,750
- My goodness!

529
00:22:39,833 --> 00:22:41,958
You're definitely a handful,
little girl.

530
00:22:42,041 --> 00:22:43,625
Now let me ask you something.

531
00:22:43,708 --> 00:22:45,083
Have you put
the least bit of thought

532
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:46,875
into what I said to you earlier?

533
00:22:46,958 --> 00:22:48,583
Tell me,
why exactly do you think

534
00:22:48,666 --> 00:22:49,708
Geuse and I were chasing you?

535
00:22:49,791 --> 00:22:50,583
- Uh...

536
00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:53,791
I-I can explain.

537
00:22:53,875 --> 00:22:56,041
The fairies said
we should go outside and play,

538
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:57,791
so, I, uh...

539
00:22:57,875 --> 00:22:59,708
- Seriously, Emilia,

540
00:22:59,791 --> 00:23:01,708
you shouldn't blame things
on other people,

541
00:23:01,791 --> 00:23:03,000
fairies or otherwise.

542
00:23:03,083 --> 00:23:04,083
- [moans]

543
00:23:04,166 --> 00:23:06,833
You're right. I'm sorry.

544
00:23:06,916 --> 00:23:09,166
Since I made friends
with Geuse while I was out,

545
00:23:09,250 --> 00:23:11,958
I only wanted to find a way
to tell you about it.

546
00:23:12,041 --> 00:23:13,541
And since he's a crybaby,

547
00:23:13,625 --> 00:23:15,916
I felt like I had to do
my part to help him.

548
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,875
- Now, that feeling is
something very special.

549
00:23:18,958 --> 00:23:21,125
However, you made
a solemn oath to me

550
00:23:21,208 --> 00:23:23,625
that you'd never go
to that place, didn't you?

551
00:23:23,708 --> 00:23:25,125
- Eh, yes, I did.

552
00:23:25,208 --> 00:23:29,958
- Well, then, you needed
to keep your word.

553
00:23:30,041 --> 00:23:32,125
- [moans]

554
00:23:32,208 --> 00:23:33,583
- Listen carefully.

555
00:23:33,666 --> 00:23:35,875
A promise
is the embodiment of trust,

556
00:23:35,958 --> 00:23:38,791
and to break it
is to betray that trust,

557
00:23:38,875 --> 00:23:40,875
so you mustn't ever do it again.

558
00:23:40,958 --> 00:23:43,416
You have to promise me, Emilia.

559
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:45,833
I want you to swear
that you'll do your best

560
00:23:45,916 --> 00:23:48,000
to keep your vows
from this moment on.

561
00:23:48,083 --> 00:23:51,000
- All right. I will.

562
00:23:51,083 --> 00:23:51,791
[crying]

563
00:23:51,875 --> 00:23:56,166
I'm really,
really sorry, Mother.

564
00:23:56,250 --> 00:23:57,166
- Okay.

565
00:23:58,166 --> 00:24:00,000
That's good enough for me.

566
00:24:00,083 --> 00:24:03,750
- [crying]

567
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:05,833
[Geuse crying]

568
00:24:05,916 --> 00:24:07,500
- And what about you, Geuse?

569
00:24:07,583 --> 00:24:08,500
Are you all right?

570
00:24:08,583 --> 00:24:09,708
- I-I'm sorry.

571
00:24:09,791 --> 00:24:12,000
I-It was just
such a dazzling sight.

572
00:24:12,083 --> 00:24:14,583
I couldn't--
I couldn't hold back my tears.

573
00:24:14,666 --> 00:24:16,541
- [laughs]

574
00:24:16,625 --> 00:24:18,500
- Uh...

575
00:24:18,583 --> 00:24:20,666
- Anyway, Emilia.
- Eh?

576
00:24:20,750 --> 00:24:22,958
- You mentioned
that fairies talked to you?

577
00:24:23,041 --> 00:24:25,333
- Oh. Uh, yes, they do,

578
00:24:25,416 --> 00:24:27,916
and they've been coming to
help me out for a long time now.

579
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:29,750
- Wanna see?
- Huh?

580
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:34,375
[gasps] Are these
lesser spirits?

581
00:24:34,458 --> 00:24:36,958
I can't believe
how many there are!

582
00:24:42,041 --> 00:24:43,833
- A wonderful surprise, indeed.

583
00:24:43,916 --> 00:24:45,791
Miss Emilia possesses
the natural talent

584
00:24:45,875 --> 00:24:47,083
to be a spirit user.

585
00:24:47,166 --> 00:24:48,875
- Lesser spirits?

586
00:24:48,958 --> 00:24:51,083
And what do you mean
by "spirit user"?

587
00:24:51,166 --> 00:24:53,041
- The things
you've been calling fairies

588
00:24:53,125 --> 00:24:56,208
are actually beings
known as lesser spirits.

589
00:24:56,291 --> 00:24:58,958
Those who communicate with them,
form contracts with them,

590
00:24:59,041 --> 00:25:02,041
and borrow their powers
are known as spirit users.

591
00:25:02,125 --> 00:25:03,750
- You mean
I can be one of them?

592
00:25:03,833 --> 00:25:05,958
- Hold on.

593
00:25:06,041 --> 00:25:08,041
Please don't give her
any crazy ideas.

594
00:25:08,125 --> 00:25:09,625
- I must point out
that Miss Emilia

595
00:25:09,708 --> 00:25:12,250
won't be a little girl forever.
Knowing that,

596
00:25:12,333 --> 00:25:14,583
at times in the future
when nobody's by her side,

597
00:25:14,666 --> 00:25:15,583
they'll be a great source
of strength for her.

598
00:25:15,666 --> 00:25:19,250
- Maybe, but that sounds
like it could be dangerous.

599
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:20,583
I can't let my sweet Emilia--

600
00:25:20,666 --> 00:25:22,000
- Eh?

601
00:25:22,083 --> 00:25:24,791
- Listen!
I'm on Geuse's side today!

602
00:25:24,875 --> 00:25:27,250
He says I'm gonna be
a spirit user. So there!

603
00:25:27,333 --> 00:25:28,250
- Nyah!
- You see?

604
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:30,250
She's taken you seriously.

605
00:25:30,333 --> 00:25:31,958
So what are you going to do now?

606
00:25:32,041 --> 00:25:33,625
- Oh, uh, well, I--

607
00:25:33,708 --> 00:25:35,250
uh, I don't know.

608
00:25:35,333 --> 00:25:36,916
I, uh...

609
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:38,333
What a predicament.

610
00:25:39,791 --> 00:25:40,958
- Hmm?

611
00:25:41,041 --> 00:25:44,125
You know, the way
that you two are carrying on,

612
00:25:44,208 --> 00:25:44,916
you're acting like
a mommy and daddy.

613
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,875
- Wha--

614
00:25:48,250 --> 00:25:50,125
D-Don't say
silly things like that!

615
00:25:50,208 --> 00:25:51,375
Geuse and I have known
each other for a long time,

616
00:25:51,458 --> 00:25:53,250
- that's all!
- Yes, that's right,

617
00:25:53,333 --> 00:25:54,708
- Miss Emilia!
- That's why we speak--

618
00:25:54,791 --> 00:25:56,500
- To one who's lived
as long as I have,

619
00:25:56,583 --> 00:25:58,291
even Miss Fortuna
is little more than a child.

620
00:25:58,375 --> 00:26:01,500
- [groans] Now I think that
may be going a bit too far.

621
00:26:01,583 --> 00:26:04,000
I'll admit you are older,
but do you even know my age?

622
00:26:04,083 --> 00:26:05,791
- No! Wait! I didn't mean to--

623
00:26:05,875 --> 00:26:07,625
Just poor phrasing! I'm sorry!

624
00:26:07,708 --> 00:26:10,125
Of course I'm quite aware
of your precise age,

625
00:26:10,208 --> 00:26:12,625
and you are
certainly far too beautiful

626
00:26:12,708 --> 00:26:15,000
and too mature
to be a mere child.

627
00:26:16,750 --> 00:26:18,125
- Mm-hmm.

628
00:26:18,208 --> 00:26:19,958
Very well, then.
I'll forgive you.

629
00:26:20,041 --> 00:26:20,958
- [gasps]

630
00:26:21,041 --> 00:26:22,875
- But look,

631
00:26:22,958 --> 00:26:23,875
you'd better be really sorry.

632
00:26:23,958 --> 00:26:26,750
- Uh, of course.

633
00:26:26,833 --> 00:26:29,666
What I was trying to say,
though poorly,

634
00:26:29,750 --> 00:26:32,750
is that I've known Miss Fortuna
for a long, long time,

635
00:26:32,833 --> 00:26:34,291
more years
than you could imagine.

636
00:26:34,375 --> 00:26:35,583
In fact, I've known her

637
00:26:35,666 --> 00:26:37,125
since the days
when your mother and father--

638
00:26:37,208 --> 00:26:37,833
- [gasps] Geuse!
- [gasps]

639
00:26:37,916 --> 00:26:41,833
Oh! Forgive me.

640
00:26:41,916 --> 00:26:43,083
- But what about
my mother and father?

641
00:26:43,166 --> 00:26:45,875
["Believe in you" playing]

642
00:26:48,083 --> 00:26:49,791
- I'm sorry, Emilia.

643
00:26:49,875 --> 00:26:50,625
- Huh?

644
00:26:50,708 --> 00:26:53,291
- We'll talk about that
another time.

645
00:26:53,375 --> 00:26:55,791
Go on back to your room now.

646
00:26:56,416 --> 00:26:58,791
- Hope you don't forget.

647
00:26:58,875 --> 00:27:02,333
I'm gonna hold you
to that, okay? [groans]

648
00:27:02,416 --> 00:27:03,708
[exhales]

649
00:27:03,791 --> 00:27:05,125
- Come on. Be a good girl.

650
00:27:05,208 --> 00:27:07,041
I know you can do that.

651
00:27:07,125 --> 00:27:08,083
And if you're extra, extra good,

652
00:27:08,166 --> 00:27:11,041
I'll let you see Geuse again
soon, too, all right?

653
00:27:11,125 --> 00:27:11,666
- You really mean it?

654
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:13,125
You'll make a solemn vow,

655
00:27:13,208 --> 00:27:15,416
and you won't break it?

656
00:27:16,916 --> 00:27:18,291
- [chuckles]

657
00:27:18,958 --> 00:27:20,625
- [gasps]

658
00:27:23,166 --> 00:27:26,333
- Yes. You have my word.

659
00:27:26,416 --> 00:27:30,041
It'll be a very important
promise, okay,

660
00:27:30,125 --> 00:27:31,958
an oath sworn between us both.

661
00:27:33,791 --> 00:27:36,000
- [grunts]
That's good enough for me.

662
00:27:36,083 --> 00:27:38,625
Thank you.
I'll go back to my room now.

663
00:27:42,208 --> 00:27:43,708
- Uh...

664
00:27:43,791 --> 00:27:45,791
- I'll see you soon, Geuse.

665
00:27:45,875 --> 00:27:47,541
Just be sure not to cry
too much, all right?

666
00:27:47,625 --> 00:27:50,791
Make it a promise
until we both meet again.

667
00:27:52,375 --> 00:27:53,875
- As you wish.

668
00:27:53,958 --> 00:27:54,833
Because I'm certain

669
00:27:54,916 --> 00:27:56,333
we'll meet again soon as well.

670
00:27:56,416 --> 00:27:58,416
[singing in Japanese]

671
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,333
- There's someone
approaching now.

672
00:28:07,416 --> 00:28:09,500
- Oh? [gasps]

673
00:28:09,583 --> 00:28:10,541
[song ends]

674
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:14,791
- [both gasp]
- GEUSE: Huh?

675
00:28:14,875 --> 00:28:17,166
[ominous music playing]

676
00:28:17,250 --> 00:28:18,166
- Huh?

677
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:21,333
- Who are you?

678
00:28:29,791 --> 00:28:31,458
- I do believe when you
want to know someone's name,

679
00:28:31,541 --> 00:28:34,416
it's considered common courtesy

680
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:36,291
to give your own first,
is it not?

681
00:28:36,375 --> 00:28:39,291
We've never seen one another
before, now, have we?

682
00:28:39,375 --> 00:28:40,458
Therefore, I feel
we should be on equal footing

683
00:28:40,541 --> 00:28:44,125
as far as building
a relationship goes.

684
00:28:44,208 --> 00:28:46,708
What gives you the right to
demand my name ahead of yours?

685
00:28:46,791 --> 00:28:48,333
You think you're
so much better than I am?

686
00:28:48,416 --> 00:28:49,791
- I think I've heard enough.

687
00:28:49,875 --> 00:28:52,125
For a man, you sure like
talking a lot, don't you?

688
00:28:52,208 --> 00:28:53,333
- Oh, "for a man," you say?

689
00:28:53,416 --> 00:28:55,416
Thanks for showing me
you don't even know any men

690
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:57,250
you could possibly
compare me to.

691
00:28:57,333 --> 00:28:59,000
My, what an attitude.

692
00:28:59,083 --> 00:29:00,041
I can't just
let that slide, you know.

693
00:29:00,125 --> 00:29:03,333
Doing so would mean
disrespecting my individuality,

694
00:29:03,416 --> 00:29:04,916
my authority, and my--

695
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:06,041
- I said enough!

696
00:29:06,125 --> 00:29:08,041
Stop talking like you're
in love with yourself,

697
00:29:08,125 --> 00:29:09,458
and tell me who you are!

698
00:29:09,541 --> 00:29:10,916
[dramatic music playing]

699
00:29:15,166 --> 00:29:19,541
- [chuckles]

700
00:29:21,583 --> 00:29:23,500
I'm the Sin Archbishop
of the Witch's Cult,

701
00:29:23,583 --> 00:29:25,333
representing Greed,

702
00:29:25,416 --> 00:29:27,333
Regulus Corneas.

